==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[Persian]] word [[شاه]] ([[shah]]).

===Pronunciation===
*chĕs, /ʧɛs/, /<tt>tSEs</tt>/

===Noun===
'''chess''' (''[[uncountable]]'')
# A two-player game played with a board of eight rows of eight squares of alternating colours and 16 [[piece]]s for each player: eight [[pawn]]s, two [[knight]]s, two [[rook]]s, two [[bishop]]s, a [[queen]] and a [[king]]; the aim is to get the opponent's king in a position on the board such that it cannot avoid being captured (the state known as [[checkmate]]).

